						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 1499 (1577 A.D.)</hi></p>						

						<p>Registers an endowment of the village Paḻambūṭṭai situated in Nallūrśīrmai and yielding an income of 415 <hi rend="italic">paṇam</hi> as <hi rend="italic">poliyūṭṭu,</hi> by <hi rend="italic">Rāyasam</hi> Tirumalaiyan, son of Timmarasa. The record is dated in <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1499, Īśvara, Mēsha, ba. 3, Anurādhā, Friday corresponding to 1577 A.D., April 5, Friday.</hi> </p>						

						</summary>
